cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI

This paper discusses the challenges of working with Web archives and proposes a methodology for extracting and studying sub-collections focused on specific topics and events. This approach involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for extracting relevant content from the archives, as well as natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.DL) for analyzing the content. The paper also discusses the societal implications of the Web archives, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
